The paper discusses empirical validation of theoretical proposals in Bayesian Deep Learning, which is a sub-field of machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on the regression experiment on UCI datasets, which falls under the category of supervised learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of Monte Carlo dropout, which is a technique commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also mentions the comparison of different methods, which falls under the category of algorithmic development (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the importance of using identical experimental setups, which is relevant to the category of systems and control (cs.SY) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
